  <prompt>
    <goal>Create a generic, reusable KanbanBoard component that wraps @hello-pangea/dnd DragDropContext and renders typed columns with cards.</goal>
    <context>
      This component goes in components/shared/ and must have ZERO domain-specific logic.
      It accepts generic typed columns and a renderCard function, making it reusable for any
      future Kanban-style UI (project tasks, document review pipeline, etc.).

      The component uses DragDropContext from @hello-pangea/dnd and delegates column rendering
      to KanbanColumn (task 011). The onDragEnd callback is passed through to the consumer.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - TypeScript generics: KanbanBoard&lt;T&gt; where T is the item type
      - NO SmartToDo-specific imports, types, or logic
      - Fluent v9 tokens for all styling (makeStyles/Griffel)
      - Horizontal flex layout for columns (equal-width, gap between)
      - Must support dark mode via semantic tokens
      - Must pass keyboard accessibility requirements
      - ADR-012: Shared component, reusable across the application
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
